{"TopicId":24209,"ForumId":18,"TopicTitle":"My homework","CreatedByName":"TerrificToby","CreatedById":58095,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-04-26T16:31:03Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"TerrificToby","CreatedById":58095,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-04-26T16:31:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EHi all,\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EGot a bit of homework that includes a question on Loci, i was completely baffled, can anyone help?\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EToby\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Awaras","CreatedById":15671,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-04-26T16:42:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EMath, biology or some other subject?\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TerrificToby","CreatedById":58095,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-04-26T16:43:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003Emathamatics\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Awaras","CreatedById":15671,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-04-26T16:44:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Locus_(mathematics)\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Locus_(mathematics)\u003C/a\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TerrificToby","CreatedById":58095,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-04-26T16:48:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003Enot really helpful, i was hoping someone could explain it.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"astropapi1","CreatedById":57507,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-04-26T16:50:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ETry yahoo. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Awaras","CreatedById":15671,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-04-26T16:50:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EWhat is the question exactly?\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TerrificToby","CreatedById":58095,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-04-26T16:51:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003Ebit hard to explain, just need an explanation.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Awaras","CreatedById":15671,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-04-26T17:07:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EBasically, you know how whenever you draw a graph of a function, you use a couple of numbers for one of the variables (-1,0,1,2 etc..), get the result for the other variable, place dots on the graph at the coordinates you got this way and then play connect-the-dots to get the graph of the function? Well, a set of all possible dots for that function is the locus... \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.mathsisfun.com/definitions/locus.html\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://www.mathsisfun.com/definitions/locus.html\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.subtangent.com/maths/loci1.php\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://www.subtangent.com/maths/loci1.php\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.onlinemathlearning.com/locus-math.html\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://www.onlinemathlearning.com/locus-math.html\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022http://www.mathopenref.com/locus.html\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://www.mathopenref.com/locus.html\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}